## convert datatype to category for efficient processing
for col in Diabetic_dataset.columns:
    if col !='Age':
        Diabetic_dataset[col] = Diabetic_dataset[col].astype('category')
        
X = Diabetic_dataset.drop(columns=['class'])
y = Diabetic_dataset['class']
X = StandardScaler().fit_transform(X)

## split data set into training,tuning and testing 60:20:20 ratio
X_train, X_left, y_train, y_left = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.40, random_state=10)
X_tuning, X_test, y_tuning, y_test = train_test_split(X_left, y_left, test_size=0.50, random_state=10)

## Tunning data set used for finding efficient hyperparameter for models

f1score=[]
Sensitivity=[]
Accuracy=[]

for i in np.arange(0.1,20,0.5):
    
    clf=LogisticRegression(C=i,max_iter=1000).fit(X_tuning, y_tuning)
    
    predictions = clf.predict(X_tuning)
    tn, fp, fn, tp = metrics.confusion_matrix(y_tuning, predictions).ravel()
    TPR = tp / (tp+fn)
    
    f1score.append(metrics.f1_score(y_tuning, predictions))                                                                                                   
    Sensitivity.append(TPR)
    Accuracy.append(clf.score(X_tuning, y_tuning))  

plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))
plt.plot(list(np.arange(0.1,20,0.5)),f1score,label='f1score') 
plt.plot(list(np.arange(0.1,20,0.5)),Sensitivity,label='Sensitivity')
plt.plot(list(np.arange(0.1,20,0.5)),Accuracy,label='Accuracy')
plt.xlabel("Value of C")
plt.title("Choice of Inverse of regularization strength for logistic regression")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

Sensitivity=[]

## Modelling on traning  dataset- Validation of traning,testing and tuning dataset result 

threshold = np.sum(1*(y_train==1))/len(y_train)   

names = ["Nearest Neighbors", "Linear SVM", "Decision Tree","Logistic Regression","Random Forest","hybrid"]

classifiers = [
    KNeighborsClassifier(3),
    SVC(kernel="linear", C=0.7,random_state=0),
    DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=5,random_state=0),
    RandomForestClassifier(max_depth=6,random_state=0),
    LogisticRegression(C=11,max_iter=1000,random_state=0),
    LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000)]


Y_pred = pd.DataFrame() # Declare a panda
Y_pred['Class_true'] = y_test

Y_pred_train = pd.DataFrame() # Declare a panda
Y_pred_train['Class_true'] = y_train

Y_pred_tuning = pd.DataFrame() # Declare a panda
Y_pred_tuning['Class_true'] = y_tuning


Y_results_test = pd.DataFrame(columns = ['Classifier','TP','FP','TN','FN','Precision','Recall','F1_score','Accuracy','Specificity','Sensitivity'])

Y_results_train = pd.DataFrame(columns = ['Classifier','TP','FP','TN','FN','Precision','Recall','F1_score','Accuracy','Specificity','Sensitivity'])

Y_results_tuning = pd.DataFrame(columns = ['Classifier','TP','FP','TN','FN','Precision','Recall','F1_score','Accuracy','Specificity','Sensitivity'])


# iterate over classifiers
for name, clf in zip(names, classifiers):
    
    if name == "Hybrid":
        Z = np.round(np.median(Y_pred,axis=1),0).astype(int)
        Y_pred[name] = Z
    else:  
        clf.fit(X_train, y_train)

        # Testing performance
        score = clf.score(X_test, y_test)

        if hasattr(clf, "decision_function"):
            Z = clf.decision_function(X_test)
            Z = clf.predict(X_test)
            Y_pred[name] = Z
        else:
            Z = clf.predict_proba(X_test)
            Z = Z[:,1]                                                # Label for class 1
            Y_pred[name] = 1*(Z>threshold)

    TP_output = 1*((Y_pred['Class_true']==1) & (Y_pred[name] == 1))
    FP_output = 1*((Y_pred['Class_true']==0) & (Y_pred[name] == 1))
    TN_output = 1*((Y_pred['Class_true']==0) & (Y_pred[name] == 0))
    FN_output = 1*((Y_pred['Class_true']==1) & (Y_pred[name] == 0))

    TP = np.sum(TP_output)
    FP = np.sum(FP_output)
    TN = np.sum(TN_output)
    FN = np.sum(FN_output)
    TPR = TP/(TP+FN)          # True positive rate
    TNR = TN/(TN+FP)          # True negative rate
    Pr = TP/(TP+FP)
    Re = TP/(TP+FN)
    acc = (TP+TN)/(TP+FP+FN+TN)
    bal_acc = (TPR+TNR)/2
    F1 = 2*(Pr*Re)/(Pr+Re)
        
    Y_results_test = Y_results_test.append({'Classifier': name, 'TP': TP,'FP': FP,'TN': TN,'FN': FN,'Precision': Pr,'Recall': Re,'F1_score': F1,'Accuracy': acc,'Specificity': TNR,'Sensitivity': TPR},ignore_index=True)

##################################################    
    # Training performance
    if name == 'Hybrid':
        Z = np.round(np.median(Y_pred_train,axis=1),0).astype(int)
        Y_pred_train[name] = Z
    else:
        score = clf.score(X_train, y_train)

        if hasattr(clf, "decision_function"):
            Z = clf.decision_function(X_train)

            Z = clf.predict(X_train)
            Y_pred_train[name] = Z
        else:
            Z = clf.predict_proba(X_train)
            Z = Z[:,1]                                                

            Y_pred_train[name] = 1*(Z>threshold)
        
    TP_output = 1*((Y_pred_train['Class_true']==1) & (Y_pred_train[name] == 1))
    FP_output = 1*((Y_pred_train['Class_true']==0) & (Y_pred_train[name] == 1))
    TN_output = 1*((Y_pred_train['Class_true']==0) & (Y_pred_train[name] == 0))
    FN_output = 1*((Y_pred_train['Class_true']==1) & (Y_pred_train[name] == 0))

    TP = np.sum(TP_output) 
    FP = np.sum(FP_output) 
    TN = np.sum(TN_output) 
    FN = np.sum(FN_output) 
    TPR = TP/(TP+FN)          # True positive rate
    TNR = TN/(TN+FP)          # True negative rate
    Pr = TP/(TP+FP)
    Re = TP/(TP+FN)
    acc = (TP+TN)/(TP+FP+FN+TN)
    bal_acc = (TPR+TNR)/2
    F1 = 2*(Pr*Re)/(Pr+Re)
        
    Y_results_train = Y_results_train.append({'Classifier': name, 'TP': TP,'FP': FP,'TN': TN,'FN': FN,'Precision': Pr,'Recall': Re,'F1_score': F1,'Accuracy': acc,'Specificity': TNR,'Sensitivity': TPR},ignore_index=True)
   
    if name == "Hybrid":
        Z = np.round(np.median(Y_pred_tuning,axis=1),0).astype(int)
        Y_pred_tuning[name] = Z
    else:  
        clf.fit(X_train, y_train)

        # Testing performance
        score = clf.score(X_tuning, y_tuning)

        if hasattr(clf, "decision_function"):
            Z = clf.decision_function(X_tuning)
            Z = clf.predict(X_tuning)
            Y_pred_tuning[name] = Z
        else:
            Z = clf.predict_proba(X_tuning)
            Z = Z[:,1]                                                # Label for class 1
            Y_pred_tuning[name] = 1*(Z>threshold)

    TP_output = 1*((Y_pred_tuning['Class_true']==1) & (Y_pred_tuning[name] == 1))
    FP_output = 1*((Y_pred_tuning['Class_true']==0) & (Y_pred_tuning[name] == 1))
    TN_output = 1*((Y_pred_tuning['Class_true']==0) & (Y_pred_tuning[name] == 0))
    FN_output = 1*((Y_pred_tuning['Class_true']==1) & (Y_pred_tuning[name] == 0))

    TP = np.sum(TP_output)
    FP = np.sum(FP_output)
    TN = np.sum(TN_output)
    FN = np.sum(FN_output)
    TPR = TP/(TP+FN)          # True positive rate
    TNR = TN/(TN+FP)          # True negative rate
    Pr = TP/(TP+FP)
    Re = TP/(TP+FN)
    acc = (TP+TN)/(TP+FP+FN+TN)
    bal_acc = (TPR+TNR)/2
    F1 = 2*(Pr*Re)/(Pr+Re)
        
    Y_results_tuning = Y_results_tuning.append({'Classifier': name, 'TP': TP,'FP': FP,'TN': TN,'FN': FN,'Precision': Pr,'Recall': Re,'F1_score': F1,'Accuracy': acc,'Specificity': TNR,'Sensitivity': TPR},ignore_index=True)


    print('Finished running analysis for', name)

## Decision tree visulization code

from sklearn import tree

Diabetic_dataset=pd.read_csv('diabetes_data_upload.csv')
Diabetic_dataset=Diabetic_dataset.replace(to_replace=['No', 'Yes'], value=[0, 1])
Diabetic_dataset['Gender']=Diabetic_dataset.Gender.replace(to_replace=['Male', 'Female'], value=[0, 1])
Diabetic_dataset['class']=Diabetic_dataset['class'].replace(to_replace=['Positive', 'Negative'], value=['Diabetes', 'NonDiabetes'])

for col in Diabetic_dataset.columns:
    if col !='Age':
        Diabetic_dataset[col] = Diabetic_dataset[col].astype('category')
        
X = Diabetic_dataset.drop(columns=['class'])
y = Diabetic_dataset['class']

X_train, X_left, y_train, y_left = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=0.30, random_state=25)
X_tuning, X_test, y_tuning, y_test = train_test_split(X_left, y_left, test_size=0.50, random_state=10)

X_names = X_train.columns.values
Y_names = y_train.unique()

clf=DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=3).fit(X_train,y_train)
text_representation = tree.export_text(clf)

print(text_representation)

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(25,15))

_=tree.plot_tree(clf, feature_names=X_names, class_names = Y_names,
                   filled=True)

## Association rules and frequent symptoms

##pip install apriori_python

from apriori_python import apriori

positive_data=Diabetic_dataset['class']=='Diabetes'
Diabetic_dataset_positive=Diabetic_dataset[positive_data]
Diabetic_dataset_positive=Diabetic_dataset_positive.drop(columns=['Age'])
Diabetic_dataset_positive.reset_index(inplace=True)

result = Diabetic_dataset_positive.set_index('index').stack().reset_index()
result = result.rename(columns={'index':'caseNo','level_1':'description', 0:'value'})
cond=result['value']==1
result1=result[cond]
result1.drop(columns=['value'],inplace=True)


list1=result1.groupby('caseNo').description.apply(list)


freqItemSet, rules = apriori(list1, minSup=0.55, minConf=0.8)
